# Automated Text-to-Video System – Module 4B (Subtitles, Polish & Documentation)

## Contributor

**Afia Noor**
Role: Subtitles, Polish & Documentation (Module 4B)

## Overview

This module focuses on improving the final video quality by adding subtitles, title/end screens, and preparing professional documentation. The goal is to ensure the generated videos are clear, presentable, and submission-ready.

## Features Implemented

* Automatic subtitles synchronized with narration text
* Styled subtitles (font, color, stroke for readability)
* Title screen (Story 1)
* End screen (Thanks for Watching)
* Final video rendering using MoviePy

## Sample Videos

* Exactly **3 sample videos** created
* Each video ~30 seconds
* Each includes subtitles, title screen, and end screen

## How to Run

```bash
python add_subtitles.py
```

Ensure the following folders exist:

* `input_videos/`
* `output_videos/`

## Folder Structure

```
subtitle_project/
│── add_subtitles.py
│── fixed_scene_data.json
│── requirements.txt
│── input_videos/
│── output_videos/
```

## Output

Final video is generated inside `output_videos/` with subtitles and polish applied.
